[SN]TITLE[SN]
Rio Olympics 2016: Park Sangyoung wins individual epee gold for South Korea

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Park Sangyoung completed a surprise victory in the men's individual epee to win gold for South Korea.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Sangyoung, 20, overturned a 14-9 deficit to beat Hungarian veteran Geza Imre 15-14.
Find out how to get into fencing with our special guide.
The Korean was appearing in his first Games while Imre, who won bronze in his first Olympics in 1996, was competing in his fifth.
France's Gauthier Grumier claimed bronze with a 15-11 victory over Swiss Benjamin Steffen.
